- untangle/split "parties" folder (e.g., move PartyProtocol to sub folder)
- injection (e.g., NetworkManager)
- create interfaces for providers (e.g., IdentityProvider)
- don't allow multiple classes to use the same objects (e.g., PartyFactory has many objects in the constructor -- but most of these are pushed down to PartyInternal)
- don't expose objects from multiple places (e.g., PartyFeedProvider from PartyInternal)
